indicator.description:
-. CRMA exercise completed in all four target villages in West Darfur and reports produced.
-Conflict assessment conducted in four target return villages in West Darfur State.
-Number of Returnees households provided with productive  assets;
- Number of Returnees  households provided with livelihoods support packages;
- Number and type of  Community infrastructure rehabilitated/ constructed and used by the community
- Number of villages that have implemented the village gender action plan.
-Number of Inclusive and gender sensitive CBOs and  community structures  established in each village 
-Percentage  of assets that have effective  management group;

target.comment:
1.1 Risk mapping in four target villages completed and gender disaggregated report produced
1.2. Conflict assessment to be conducted in all four target villages and report to be produced to inform planning and programming;
2.1	200 of resettled households own and use productive assets
2.2   200 households use fuel efficient stoves and other identified items regularly
3.1 Community infrastructure are rehabilitated/ constructed and used. 
	Four water points constructed in the 4 target villages; 
	Community  Centre constructed in each of the 4 villages ; 
	Grinding mills made available in each of the four villages;
3.2	2000 working days are provided in each village.
3.3  40%  of women in 4 villages feel secure and reduced workload due to use of gender sensitive construction/rehabilitation community infrastructure (perception survey)
4.1	Four CBOs are established and functional in each of the 4 villages
4.2	 All newly established community infrastructure with active management committee participation.
4.3	 Dialogues and discussions of village priorities and affairs are increased in inclusive and gender sensitive manners.

indicator.description:
1.  Number of ex-combatants and associated groups, demobilized & reintegrated, disaggregated by age, gender and disability;

2.  Percentage of participants that report successful individual reintegration projects in client satisfaction surveys

3.  # of pilot  SR/ CSAC projects implemented; 
4.  # of communities  and DDR participants provided with psychosocial support
5.  # of best practices and lessons learnt as the result of  implementation of SR/CSAC projects reflected in the CSAC strategy implementation plans for the next year

baseline.comment:
-- Disaster and environment plans and strategies are not adequately implemented due to inadequate resources and awareness;
-- No National Disaster  Management Plan in place to describe strategies and stakeholder roles on Disaster Risk Reduction Management (DRRM)
-- A weakly functioning early warning system exists in Sudan, which leads to enhanced exposure of communities to natural hazards; 
--Scattered information on disaster risks exist, but no comprehensive risk analysis available for Sudan;

target.comment:
-- National Task Forces on Disaster Risk Reduction/Management (DRRM) formed, inclusive of specialized women’s organizations;
-- Training courses on gender-sensitive DRR organized for the National Task Forces members 
-- Draft of the National Disaster Management started
-- National Early Warning committee conducted, consultations to identify bottlenecks and define strategies for effective warning dissemination started
--- Necessary equipment provided to  relevant early warning units to improve their capacities for warning dissemination to stakeholders and communities;

-- At least 5 national and state level consultations held on the draft  National Disaster Risk Reduction Management Strategy, with representation  of specialized women’s organizations; 
-- The 1st draft National Disaster Risk Reduction Management Strategy prepared
-- A Sudan Disaster Risk Profile report produced inclusive of gender-based analysis,
-- Data collection and analysis started on disaster risk assessment;
-- Hazard maps for flood, drought and other key hazards collected for Sudan; 
-- Dissemination of early warning instruments to stakeholders and men and women in local communities prepared for;
